SIMPLE: successor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Successor
<hw>Suc*ces"sor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>successour</ets>, OF. <ets>successur</ets>, <ets>successor</ets>,
F. <ets>successeur</ets>, L. <ets>successor</ets>. See
<er>Succeed</er>.]</ety> <def>One who succeeds or follows; one who takes
the place which another has left, and sustains the like part or
character; -- correlative to <xex>predecessor</xex>; <as>as, the
<ex>successor</ex> of a deceased king</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A gift to a corporation, either of lands or of chattels, without
naming their <qex>successors</qex>, vests an absolute property in them
so lond as the corporation subsists.</q>
<rj><qau>Blackstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Succiduous</ent>⟦br⟧
